    // Final Result section
    div(class="body_container light")
      section#result
        div(class="center_align")
          h3 · &nbsp;&nbsp;Final Result&nbsp;&nbsp; ·

        p In order to get a better user experience for interaction and usability, I switched all previous prototype pages from InVision to Proto.io. The reason is that InVision uses static wireframes to prototype, but Proto.io helps to create a fully interactive prototype that feels more real.

        p After I update the prototype in Proto.io, the couples that were interviewed at the beginning of the project were asked to try out the prototype and asked for feedback. This is user test, checking if the designed features can actually help them to achieve their goals. With the feedback, I modified some interaction preferences in the prototype.

    // Reflection section
    div(class="body_container dark")
      section#reflection
        div(class="center_align")
          h3 · &nbsp;&nbsp;My Reflection&nbsp;&nbsp; ·

        p At the beginning of the project, I have suggested building an app for couples only, I have tried out a few relationship apps, and it does not fully fulfil my requirements of managing information for my relationship. So I wish to build a customized app to be used by different couples, allowing the couples to build up and manage a private space belonging to the two only.

        p For this project, I discovered it is very constrained to design for the end users when three-quarters of the team also fit in the end user criteria. This is very problematic, while the goal for the end users and the designers may differ. So I concluded that it is very important to set the right mind while designing for end users. As designers, we should focus on the end user’s goal, and do not assume for the users.



